= run-a-lot

A sinatra app analyzing and visualizing gpx/kml/nmea gps traces.


== Ruby gems needed

  * sinatra
  * nokogiri (for gpx parsing)
  * do_sqlite3 || do_postgres || do_mysql
  * dm-core
  * dm-aggregates
  * gchartrb


== Setup

MySQL:
  Just set up an empty Database and set the connections in config/config.yml

PostgreSQL:
  Just set up an empty Database and set the connections in config/config.yml

SQLite3:
  Just run it.

Google Maps:
  You need an individual API key. The one given in config.yml is for localhost, if you want to use run-a-log somewehre else, get an appropiate key.
